### Rules

- Every component MUST have ports for ALL physical pins on its package — see "Required Port Counts" below.
- Resistors/capacitors/inductors have 2 pins (passive type).
- LEDs/diodes have 2 pins (anode=passive, cathode=passive).
- ICs: use the pinout reference above for exact pin counts and names.
- Connectors: create one port per pin as specified in requirements.
- Unused pins MUST still have a port with `electrical_type: "no_connect"`.
{% if pin_count_table %}

### Required Port Counts

The validator checks that every component has the EXACT port count matching its package pin count. Missing ports cause routing failures and the netlist will be rejected.

{{ pin_count_table }}

Example: if U1 (TQFP-32) uses 20 pins in the circuit, create 20 connected ports + 12 no_connect ports = 32 total.
